*Info: Begin of commit_pushdown_eco (mem=1936.2M)

Usage: commit_pushdown_eco [-help] -eco_object_dir <dirName>
                           -post_eco_dir <dirName> -pre_eco_dir <dirName>
                           [-ptns <ptnNameList>]

-help                      # Prints out the command usage
-eco_object_dir <dirName>  # specifies the directory in which various partition
                           # sub-directories are present.Each of these
                           # partition sub-directories must contain its
                           # eco_logical.txt, eco_physical.def.gz and,
                           # optionally, eco_net.def.gz and eco_pin.txt files
                           # (string, required)
-post_eco_dir <dirName>    # specifies the post eco directory in which
                           # partition sub-directories - after eco is applied
                           # on each partition - will be saved (string, required)
-pre_eco_dir <dirName>     # specifies the directory in which various partition
                           # sub-directories - corresponding the new version of
                           # the original design - are present. Eco objects
                           # will be applied to these partitions
                           # (string, required)
-ptns <ptnNameList>        # specifies the list of partition names to apply eco
                           # (string, optional)